[Course_Description]
Reframing Organizations looks at how to structure organizations in order to simplify tasks and decision-making. It shows that there is no foolproof way to arrive at the right answer when facing complex challenges. However, certain structures exist that increase the chances of company success. This audio-only course summarizes key lessons from Lee G. Bolman and Terrence E. Deal's classic leadership book. Learn how to build self-managing teams, implement effective hiring practices, increase employee loyalty, win over stakeholders, gain public trust, and more. These tips will help you rebuild your business through a winning combination of artistry, choice, and leadership. Note: This audiobook summary was produced by Blinkist. We are pleased to host this content in our library.